Shut up.

01:49:20.119 --> 01:49:22.361
No. Agh.

01:49:28.794 --> 01:49:32.128
You know, he's gettin' ready to take a fit.
What do you care?

01:49:46.645 --> 01:49:49.183
Shh... Shh...

01:49:49.273 --> 01:49:51.729
That's better, Shh, That's better.

01:49:55.446 --> 01:49:58.151
Hey, come on,
Leave some for the rest of us.

01:50:09.085 --> 01:50:11.492
Move away from the baby.

01:50:13.255 --> 01:50:15.414
Towards me.

01:50:15.508 --> 01:50:18.877
Don't shoot.
We just wanted food.

01:50:18.969 --> 01:50:21.258
Take off your boots.

01:50:22.932 --> 01:50:26.301
Take off your pants.
Take off your shirt.

01:50:33.609 --> 01:50:35.685
Don't shoot me, please.

01:50:37.321 --> 01:50:40.607
We're starvin'.
We haven't eaten in days,

01:50:40.699 --> 01:50:45.243
Come on.
We're starving. We haven't eaten in days.

01:50:45.329 --> 01:50:47.405
Come on.

01:50:50.209 --> 01:50:52.747
Thanks. Thank you,

01:50:52.837 --> 01:50:55.162
Now you get runnin'.
I will.

01:50:55.256 --> 01:50:57.462
And keep runnin'.
Thank you.

01:51:58.027 --> 01:52:02.819
I love the snow.
I hate the snow. I hate the cold.

01:52:04.450 --> 01:52:07.570
Come on.
Fellas, what's the rush?

01:52:07.661 --> 01:52:12.158
If Ruby finds out we've spent the night.
there'll be hell to pay.

01:52:48.786 --> 01:52:51.953
'My love, where are you?

01:52:52.748 --> 01:52:56.366
'With no hope of reaching you,
I write to you,

01:52:56.460 --> 01:52:58.619
'as I always do,

01:53:00.381 --> 01:53:03.002
as I have always done.'

01:53:10.182 --> 01:53:14.560
♪ I'm alone, but I don't worry... ♪

01:53:14.645 --> 01:53:19.224
♪ 'Cause I'm sittin' on top of the world ♪

01:53:23.529 --> 01:53:26.446
You reckon we could eat this?

01:53:27.199 --> 01:53:28.741
Hey.

01:53:28.826 --> 01:53:32.740
Well, you know, you cook somethin'
long enough, you can eat anything.

01:53:32.830 --> 01:53:35.866
It's froze,
How long it been there for?

01:53:35.958 --> 01:53:38.745
You hungry?
Yeah.

01:53:38.836 --> 01:53:40.912
Not very long.

01:54:17.708 --> 01:54:19.582
Good evenin'.

01:54:19.668 --> 01:54:22.420
Hope we didn't disturb you.

01:54:22.505 --> 01:54:26.668
D'you mind if I warm myself by your fire?

01:54:27.468 --> 01:54:29.092
Name's Teague.

01:54:29.178 --> 01:54:31.847
Do I know you?
Stobrod Thewes.

01:54:33.057 --> 01:54:35.215
That your wife?
That's a 'he'.

01:54:35.309 --> 01:54:37.052
Is 'he' your wife?

01:54:37.144 --> 01:54:41.723
We're musicians.
He picks a banjo, I got a fiddle.

01:54:41.816 --> 01:54:45.185
Your sweetheart's got
a nice piece of flesh on him.

01:54:45.277 --> 01:54:48.693
He looks pretty romantic by the fire.
It's a picture of love.

01:54:55.329 --> 01:54:57.701
You gonna play that fiddle?

01:54:57.790 --> 01:54:59.450
Sure.

01:54:59.542 --> 01:55:01.499
Sure.

01:55:01.585 --> 01:55:03.661
Hey, wake up.

01:55:05.214 --> 01:55:07.254
Evenin', missis,

01:55:07.883 --> 01:55:10.553
Where's Georgia?
'Where's Georgia'?

01:55:15.015 --> 01:55:18.384
Captain Teague wants us to play now.
Love to.

01:55:18.477 --> 01:55:22.309
We heard there were some deserters up
in these parts hidden out in a big cave.

01:55:22.398 --> 01:55:25.233
Not come to my ears.
So you don't know where this big cave is?

01:55:25.317 --> 01:55:27.310
No, sir.
You do, Stobs. He means...

01:55:27.403 --> 01:55:28.683
No, right. No, no.

01:55:28.779 --> 01:55:32.694
There is a cave right up near Bearpen
Branch. We played some music up there,

01:55:32.783 --> 01:55:37.362
Never occurred to me they were outliers.
It ain't nowhere near Bearpen Branch.

01:55:37.455 --> 01:55:39.328
He's always gettin' lost.

01:55:39.415 --> 01:55:42.167
That cave... we live there.

01:55:42.251 --> 01:55:46.580
I used to freeze up in that cave
till I got gived this new coat.

01:55:46.672 --> 01:55:50.622
Ruby made me this coat.
I like my coat.

01:55:50.718 --> 01:55:54.253
This part belonged to a reverend
and this part belonged to a horse.

01:55:54.346 --> 01:55:58.973
Ruby said... what is it?...
I should pray or neigh, dependin'.

01:55:59.059 --> 01:56:01.301
He don't...
he don't know what he's sayin'.

01:56:01.395 --> 01:56:05.263
He got a mind
no bigger than a pickled walnut.

01:56:05.357 --> 01:56:08.193
It's a good coat.

01:56:10.654 --> 01:56:18.033
♪ I wish, I wish my baby was born ♪

01:56:19.288 --> 01:56:26.584
♪ And sittin' on its papa's knee ♪

01:56:26.670 --> 01:56:28.710
♪ And me, poor girl ♪

01:56:28.798 --> 01:56:34.040
♪ And me, poor girl, were dead and gone ♪

01:56:35.471 --> 01:56:43.514
♪ And the green grass growin' o'er my feet ♪

01:56:44.271 --> 01:56:51.519
♪ I ain't ahead, nor never will be ♪

01:56:53.072 --> 01:57:00.818
♪ Till the sweet apple grows ♪
♪ on a sour apple tree ♪

01:57:02.123 --> 01:57:06.535
♪ The owl, the owl ♪

01:57:06.627 --> 01:57:09.296
♪ Is a lonely bird ♪

01:57:11.048 --> 01:57:14.547
♪ It chills my heart ♪

01:57:15.344 --> 01:57:18.630
♪ With dread and terror ♪

01:57:19.765 --> 01:57:22.387
♪ That someone's blood ♪

01:57:22.476 --> 01:57:24.220
♪ Someone's blood ♪

01:57:24.311 --> 01:57:27.396
♪ There on his wing ♪

01:57:28.607 --> 01:57:32.190
♪ That someone's blood ♪

01:57:32.945 --> 01:57:36.777
♪ There on his... feather ♪

01:57:44.790 --> 01:57:46.664
Broke my young heart.

01:57:51.213 --> 01:57:53.206
We gonna be here all night?

01:57:55.885 --> 01:57:57.961
Stand over there.

01:58:09.023 --> 01:58:12.558
Ruby, she don't know
one end of the war from the other.

01:58:12.651 --> 01:58:15.688
You don't have to worry yourself about her,
is what I'm sayin'.

01:58:15.780 --> 01:58:19.113
Or Ada, neither.
You know what I'm sayin'?

01:58:19.742 --> 01:58:22.363
You too.
You stand over there.

01:58:25.498 --> 01:58:27.823
We gonna get our tintype made?

01:58:34.507 --> 01:58:36.333
Don't smile.

01:58:36.425 --> 01:58:38.003
What?
Quit smilin'.

01:58:38.094 --> 01:58:40.501
He always smiles,
He don't mean nothin' by it.

01:58:40.596 --> 01:58:43.169
I told him, there ain't nothin'
in this world worth a smile.

01:58:43.265 --> 01:58:45.803
Put your hat over your face.

01:58:52.608 --> 01:58:54.648
Cover your face with your hat.

01:59:03.452 --> 01:59:05.279
Ruby.
What?

01:59:06.038 --> 01:59:07.532
Ruby.
What's wrong?

01:59:07.623 --> 01:59:11.074
Teague... The Home Guard...
What?

01:59:12.169 --> 01:59:14.245
They shot your daddy.

01:59:14.338 --> 01:59:16.461
They shot your daddy, and Pangle too.

01:59:22.471 --> 01:59:26.718
I told Georgia he can stop here.
I told him he can sleep in the barn.

01:59:26.809 --> 01:59:30.641
He's got nothin' inside him.
He'll walk out of here and die in the snow.

01:59:30.729 --> 01:59:33.933
He can milk the cows.
I was worried about that.

01:59:36.318 --> 01:59:40.233
It's five hours' climb from here.
He drew a map.

01:59:40.322 --> 01:59:42.315
I'm ready.

01:59:43.242 --> 01:59:47.156
You know them fools
stayed the night in the mill?

01:59:47.246 --> 01:59:51.326
That's Stobrod Thewes. Can't do
one good thing without addin' the bad.

01:59:51.417 --> 01:59:55.878
Left tracks in the snow all the way up
for the Home Guard to follow,

01:59:55.963 --> 01:59:58.288
Sign that says 'Shoot me'.
Ruby...

02:00:01.635 --> 02:00:03.178
Ruby.

02:00:05.473 --> 02:00:07.512
I'm sorry.

02:00:09.518 --> 02:00:12.305
Every piece of this is man's bullshit.

02:00:12.396 --> 02:00:15.018
They call this war a cloud over the land,

02:00:15.107 --> 02:00:16.919
but they made the weather,
and then they stand

02:00:16.944 --> 02:00:19.959
in the rain and say
'Shit, it's rainin'.'

02:00:25.785 --> 02:00:30.992
If I cry one tear for my daddy,
I stole it off a crocodile.

02:00:34.668 --> 02:00:35.748
All right, then.

02:01:25.133 --> 02:01:27.173
All right, then.

02:01:28.431 --> 02:01:31.431
Dear God.

02:01:35.563 --> 02:01:37.721
Oh, dear God.

02:01:43.988 --> 02:01:46.443
He ain't here.

02:01:46.532 --> 02:01:50.399
Agh. Teague's probably took him.

02:01:50.494 --> 02:01:54.362
They did that with the Swanger boys,
didn't they?

02:01:54.457 --> 02:01:57.493
Strung 'em up, as a warnin'.

02:02:02.715 --> 02:02:04.957
They took his coat.

02:02:05.050 --> 02:02:06.924
Why would they take his coat?

02:02:12.516 --> 02:02:15.683
Daddy? Daddy.

02:02:15.770 --> 02:02:17.727
Daddy.

02:02:23.736 --> 02:02:24.934
Daddy?

02:02:25.029 --> 02:02:27.602
He's still breathin'.

02:02:27.698 --> 02:02:30.320
It's Ruby.

02:02:30.409 --> 02:02:32.153
Don't you die on me again.

02:02:38.250 --> 02:02:42.462
We gotta get him home,
He won't make it, He'll die first.

02:02:42.546 --> 02:02:45.962
He's got hardly no blood left in him.

02:02:48.761 --> 02:02:50.670
There it is, I feel it.

02:02:50.763 --> 02:02:51.842
You got it?
Yep.

02:02:52.723 --> 02:02:57.184
There's a place close.
Old Cherokee, it used to be.

02:02:57.269 --> 02:02:59.760
It's got shelter, water.

02:02:59.855 --> 02:03:02.477
I used to hide up there
when he'd get a temper goin'.

02:03:02.566 --> 02:03:04.523
God.

02:03:11.867 --> 02:03:15.995
I'll go look for some food,
Take the shotgun.

02:03:41.939 --> 02:03:43.599
Goddamn.

02:03:54.410 --> 02:03:56.486
Turn around.

02:03:57.997 --> 02:04:00.618
Go back where you came from.

02:04:02.168 --> 02:04:04.540
Go back.

02:04:08.007 --> 02:04:10.083
Ada?

02:04:10.843 --> 02:04:12.006
Ada Monroe?

02:04:13.971 --> 02:04:16.758
Turn around or I'll shoot.

02:04:45.252 --> 02:04:46.747
Inman?

02:04:46.837 --> 02:04:48.913
Inman?

02:05:02.103 --> 02:05:04.309
Inman.

02:05:36.429 --> 02:05:38.717
You better come with me.

02:05:51.068 --> 02:05:53.144
Ruby.

02:05:54.071 --> 02:05:55.649
This is Inman.

02:06:00.828 --> 02:06:03.200
Oh. Congratulations.

02:06:03.289 --> 02:06:06.824
Oughta send you out with a shotgun
a lot more.

02:06:08.586 --> 02:06:11.752
Looks if he's about to topple over.

02:06:11.839 --> 02:06:14.460
I may need to.
You shot or somethin'?

02:06:16.469 --> 02:06:18.046
Not lately.

02:06:29.440 --> 02:06:32.607
He's asleep.
I ain't surprised.

02:06:32.693 --> 02:06:36.857
Your man looked tuckered out.
I saw him.

02:06:36.947 --> 02:06:41.360
In Sally Swanger's well.
A man like a black smudge in the snow.

02:06:41.452 --> 02:06:44.488
Well, there you go.
It wasn't the same, what I saw.

02:06:44.580 --> 02:06:46.786
In the well it was as if he were falling.

02:06:46.874 --> 02:06:50.539
You probably just don't remember it right.
I remember it exactly.

02:06:50.628 --> 02:06:52.834
There were crows... black crows.

02:06:52.922 --> 02:06:55.045
They were flyin' towards me.

02:06:55.132 --> 02:06:58.584
Ruby, I thought I was seein' him fall.

02:07:00.846 --> 02:07:03.931
Instead, I was seein' him come back to me.

02:07:06.435 --> 02:07:09.769
I got big plans for that farm.

02:07:13.776 --> 02:07:16.481
I know.

02:07:16.570 --> 02:07:18.362
I know you have.

02:07:18.447 --> 02:07:22.362
I got a vision in my mind
of how Black Cove oughta be.

02:07:26.497 --> 02:07:28.786
I don't know, Ruby.

02:07:28.874 --> 02:07:33.168
All this while
I've been packin' ice around my heart.

02:07:35.714 --> 02:07:38.550
How do I make it melt?

02:07:41.512 --> 02:07:42.971
Hey.

02:07:44.056 --> 02:07:46.891
You about done with my knife?

02:07:46.976 --> 02:07:49.681
We got a bird to cook.

02:07:49.770 --> 02:07:51.562
Just about.

02:07:54.483 --> 02:07:58.267
You're makin' a pig's ear of that job.

02:07:59.739 --> 02:08:01.815
Give it to me.

02:08:07.663 --> 02:08:10.450
Oh, I ain't gonna cut you.

02:08:12.126 --> 02:08:16.337
Can't see that it'd make
a bit of difference if I did.

02:08:27.141 --> 02:08:29.347
You got the right feelings for her?

02:08:29.435 --> 02:08:32.685
Don't turn your head. Tsk.

02:08:36.442 --> 02:08:37.770
I do.

02:09:03.344 --> 02:09:06.879
I'm sorry.
I was tryin' to be quiet.

02:09:12.561 --> 02:09:14.933
Did you get my letters?

02:09:16.607 --> 02:09:18.765
I got three letters.

02:09:19.568 --> 02:09:24.361
I carried them.
I carried them in the book you gave me.

02:09:24.448 --> 02:09:25.907
The Bartram.

02:09:27.076 --> 02:09:30.492
I probably sent 103.

02:09:35.167 --> 02:09:37.741
Did you write to me?

02:09:37.837 --> 02:09:39.746
Whenever I could.

02:09:39.839 --> 02:09:42.045
If you never got them, I can summarize,

02:09:42.133 --> 02:09:44.968
No. No, no,
'I pray you are well,

02:09:45.052 --> 02:09:47.341
'I pray I am in your thoughts.

02:09:47.430 --> 02:09:52.672
You are all that keeps me
from slidin' into some dark place.'

02:09:52.768 --> 02:09:55.853
How did I keep you?

02:09:55.938 --> 02:09:58.809
We barely knew each other.
It was a few moments.

02:09:58.899 --> 02:10:00.809
A thousand moments.

02:10:03.612 --> 02:10:07.278
They're like a bag...
of tiny diamonds.

02:10:08.701 --> 02:10:12.319
Don't matter if they're real
or things I made up.

02:10:14.498 --> 02:10:16.705
The shape of your neck.

02:10:18.586 --> 02:10:21.041
That's real.

02:10:21.130 --> 02:10:25.258
The way you felt under my hands
when I pulled you to me.

02:10:36.520 --> 02:10:39.225
You were plowing a field.

02:10:40.191 --> 02:10:42.729
You were carrying a tray.

02:10:42.818 --> 02:10:45.605
You wouldn't come in.
No, I wouldn't go in.

02:10:45.696 --> 02:10:50.607
So that's why I had to carry a tray.
So I could come out to see you.

02:10:52.703 --> 02:10:55.787
That kiss.

02:10:55.873 --> 02:10:59.491
Which I kissed every day of my walking.

02:11:01.212 --> 02:11:03.335
Every day I was waiting.

02:11:04.215 --> 02:11:05.625
Longing.

02:11:05.716 --> 02:11:08.800
Longing to see your face.

02:11:15.017 --> 02:11:18.267
If you could see my inside...

02:11:18.354 --> 02:11:23.348
Now, whatever you wanna name it...
my spirit? That's what I fear.

02:11:24.401 --> 02:11:26.359
I think I'm ruined.

02:11:26.445 --> 02:11:29.945
They kept tryin' to put me in the ground.

02:11:31.200 --> 02:11:33.869
But I wasn't ready.
Inman...

02:11:33.953 --> 02:11:37.369
But if I had... if I had goodness.
I lost it.

02:11:39.583 --> 02:11:42.833
If I had anything tender in me,
I shot it dead.

02:11:44.505 --> 02:11:48.372
How could I write to you after what I done,

02:11:49.343 --> 02:11:50.422
what I seen?

02:11:50.511 --> 02:11:52.005
Number one,

02:11:52.096 --> 02:11:54.421
shut this door.
It's freezin'.

02:11:54.515 --> 02:11:57.516
Number two, shut that door.
It's freezin'.

02:11:57.601 --> 02:12:00.057
Layin' on my back,
my fingers poked in my ears,

02:12:00.146 --> 02:12:02.850
tryin' to shut out
who's got a bag of diamonds,

02:12:02.940 --> 02:12:05.229
who's carrying a tray...

02:12:05.317 --> 02:12:07.690
If you wanna get three
feet up a bull's ass,

02:12:07.778 --> 02:12:11.313
just listen to what sweethearts
whisper to one another.

02:12:11.407 --> 02:12:17.077
In fact, if y'all gonna wimble-wimble
all night, I'm gonna sleep in with him.

02:12:31.886 --> 02:12:34.721
I'll say good night,
No.

02:12:38.100 --> 02:12:40.176
Please...

02:12:41.187 --> 02:12:42.847
don't say good night.

02:13:07.671 --> 02:13:10.459
Wars make some things pointless.

02:13:14.637 --> 02:13:17.009
It's hard to imagine a wedding.

02:13:19.225 --> 02:13:22.594
I think even my father
would recognize that.

02:13:23.270 --> 02:13:25.346
Ada, I wanna marry you.

02:13:27.066 --> 02:13:29.308
If you'll have me.

02:13:30.069 --> 02:13:34.945
Isn't there some religion where you just
have to say 'I marry you' three times,

02:13:35.032 --> 02:13:37.025
and you're man and wife?

02:13:37.993 --> 02:13:40.033
I marry you.

02:13:41.122 --> 02:13:43.328
I marry you, I marry you.

02:13:48.421 --> 02:13:50.460
Why is that funny?

02:13:50.548 --> 02:13:55.174
I think it's 'I divorce you' three times
and you're not married anymore.

02:13:57.179 --> 02:13:58.590
I can wait for you.

02:13:59.223 --> 02:14:04.644
Oh, Inman,
I marry you, I marry you, I marry you.

02:14:04.728 --> 02:14:06.721
I marry you, I marry you.

02:14:14.572 --> 02:14:18.320
I have so...
I have so many buttons, Sorry.

02:14:22.037 --> 02:14:24.825
Will you turn your back?

02:14:36.051 --> 02:14:37.427
No.

02:14:39.722 --> 02:14:42.011
No, I will not.

02:16:27.121 --> 02:16:30.038
I'll lead the horse
at a pace your daddy can tolerate.

02:16:30.124 --> 02:16:33.789
You two go ahead now.
No. I don't wanna do that.

02:16:33.878 --> 02:16:36.629
No. We can all go together.
It's safer this way.

02:16:36.714 --> 02:16:39.039
We're deserters.
No one has a quarrel with you.

02:16:39.133 --> 02:16:41.290
He's right.

02:16:41.385 --> 02:16:45.334
I gather I...
I need permission from you, Ruby,

02:16:45.431 --> 02:16:48.763
if I reckon on livin' at Black Cove.

02:16:57.942 --> 02:16:59.567
All right, then.

02:17:03.531 --> 02:17:05.608
You stay on that horse.

02:17:05.700 --> 02:17:08.737
And don't lose it.
Or sell it.

02:17:09.538 --> 02:17:12.409
Gonna need it back on the farm.

02:17:15.377 --> 02:17:17.454
All right, Daddy.

02:17:21.592 --> 02:17:24.165
I don't wanna let you go.

02:17:26.972 --> 02:17:29.379
I'll be with you by nightfall.

02:17:35.064 --> 02:17:36.439
Ugh.

02:17:38.400 --> 02:17:40.477
All right, then.

02:18:11.308 --> 02:18:15.139
Hope that Georgia boy's
been tendin' to the animals.

02:18:15.228 --> 02:18:18.100
I knew you were thinkin' on him.
I was not.

02:18:18.190 --> 02:18:20.598
I was thinkin' on swollen udders.
Oh...

02:18:20.692 --> 02:18:24.940
And before you say 'same difference'...
I'm sayin' nothin'.

02:18:25.030 --> 02:18:29.491
Miss Lovey-Dovey.
Miss Lovey-Dovey.

02:18:29.576 --> 02:18:31.616
Hey.

02:18:31.704 --> 02:18:35.832
That was a long funeral for your daddy.
That was a wake.

02:18:35.915 --> 02:18:37.540
That was Irish.

02:18:39.587 --> 02:18:41.495
Now, your friend Georgia here...

02:18:41.589 --> 02:18:45.207
We went down to visit you when
